# Troubleshooting

We were able to reproduce the same issue on vLLM v0.8.0 + A800 GPU, but not on v0.8.2 + A800. The concurrency range that caused the issues is also different with a higher starting threshold at 28 vu. We performed a bisection and discovered that it was 1fe0fd12d33afb345c8e81410f2ebf60462974b6 that fixed this issue for A800 but not L20. Critically, **partially reverting the change on the `video` line in this commit will make this issue reproducible again on A800 for vLLM v0.8.2.**

We also discovered that disable prefix caching will completely fix this issue.

